@startuml rx-sequence-flow
title Rx Transaction Sequence (Happy + Error Paths)
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
actor "Prescribing EHR/\nTelehealth" as EHR
participant "Rhapsody\nFHIR/REST API" as API
participant "Validation\nLayer" as Val
participant "Routing\nEngine" as Route
database "Analytics/\nAudit" as Audit
participant "Pharmacy/\nHUB" as Pharmacy

== Happy Path ==
EHR -> API: POST /rx-bundles\n(FHIR Bundle type=transaction)
activate API
API -> Val: 1. Structural (FHIR)\n2. Business Rules\n3. Basic Semantics
activate Val
Val --> API: OK
deactivate Val
API -> Route: Apply routing rules
activate Route
Route -> Pharmacy: Rx (FHIR or legacy format)
activate Pharmacy
Pharmacy --> Route: Fulfillment ACK / Status
deactivate Pharmacy
Route -> Audit: RxEvent (success)
deactivate Route
API --> EHR: 202 Accepted\n(Location: status URL)
deactivate API

== Error Path ==
note over EHR,API: Invalid Bundle
EHR -> API: POST /rx-bundles (bad data)
API -> Val: Validation fails
Val --> API: OperationOutcome\n(issue codes, details)
API --> EHR: 400 Bad Request\n+ Error Bundle
deactivate API

note bottom: Idempotent, retryable, auditable
@enduml
